HEADWORD: Andalusite
<hw>An`da*lu"site</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A silicate of aluminium, occurring usually in thick rhombic prisms,
nearly square, of a grayish or pale reddish tint. It was first
discovered in Andalusia, Spain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Andante</ent>⟦br⟧
